Read 08 Operators and Loops


Comparison Operators: Evaluating Conditions

You can evaluate a situation by comparing one value

in the script to what you might expect it to be.

The result will be Boolean: true or false

    ==

is equal to

The operator compares two values(numbers,strings, or

Booleans) to see if they are the same.

   ===
strict equal to

The operator compares two values to check that

both the data type and value are the same.

  !=
  
is not equal to

The operator compares two values (numbers, strings, or 

Booleans) to see if they are not the same.

  !==
strict not equal to

This operator compares two values to check that both the

data type and value are not the same.

Logical Operators

Logical operatorasa allow you to compare the results

of more than one comparison operator.

         &&
         
    Logical and
  
This operator tests more than one condition.

        ||
      
     Logical or
     
This operator tests at least one condition.

         !
         
    Logical not
    
This operator takes a single Boolean value and inverts it.
  
  
